<p>Cultural importance index (CI) is calculated by the sum of the use reports (UR) of informants mentioning each species use (from 
 <italic>i</italic>
 <sub>1</sub> to 
 <italic>i</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>N</italic>
 </sub>) in each use category and adding all the UR of each category (from 
 <italic>u</italic>
 <sub>1</sub> to 
 <italic>u</italic>
 <sub>NC</sub>) divided by the total number of informants 
 <italic>N</italic>. This index is determined by the following formula [
 <xref rid="B29" ref-type="bibr">29</xref>]:
 <disp-formula id="EEq4">
  <label>(4)</label>
  <math id="M4">
   <mtable>
    <mtr>
     <mtd>
      <msub>
       <mrow>
        <mtext>CI</mtext>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mstyle displaystyle="true">
       <munderover>
        <mrow>
         <mo stretchy="true">∑</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>u</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi>u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <msub>
          <mrow>
           <mi>u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mtext>NC</mtext>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
        </mrow>
       </munderover>
       <mrow>
        <mstyle displaystyle="true">
         <munderover>
          <mrow>
           <mo stretchy="true">∑</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <mi>i</mi>
           <mo>=</mo>
           <msub>
            <mrow>
             <mi>i</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
             <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mrow>
             <mi>i</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
             <mi>N</mi>
            </mrow>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
         </munderover>
         <mrow>
          <mfrac>
           <mrow>
            <mtext>UR</mtext>
            <msub>
             <mrow>
              <mi>u</mi>
             </mrow>
             <mrow>
              <mi>i</mi>
             </mrow>
            </msub>
           </mrow>
           <mi>N</mi>
          </mfrac>
         </mrow>
        </mstyle>
       </mrow>
      </mstyle>
      <mo>,</mo>
     </mtd>
    </mtr>
   </mtable>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where CI is an ethnobotanical index that indicates the spread of the use along with the diversity of uses of each species.
</p>
